import sys
import collections

class City:
    def __init__(self, pref, year):
        self.pref = pref
        self.year = year

n, m = map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split())

pref_dic = collections.defaultdict(list)
for _ in range(m):
    p, y = map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split())
    pref_dic[p].append(City(p, y))

for p, c in sorted(pref_dic.items()):
    c.sort(key=lambda x: x.year)
    for i, city in enumerate(c, 1):
        print('{:0>6d}{:0>6d}'.format(city.pref, i))

import sys

N, M = map(int, input().split())
city = [tuple(map(int, input().split())) for i in range(M)]

l = [[] for i in range(N)]
for i in range(M):
    l[city[i][0]-1].append(city[i][1])

for i in range(N):
    l[i].sort()

for i in range(M):
    print("%06d%06d" % (city[i][0], l[city[i][0]-1].index(city[i][1]) + 1))
